<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-11-30T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-11-30T14:00:00-05:00" n="728" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d728">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">881.00/1719a: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Matthews</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-11-30T14:00:00-05:00">November 30, 1940—2 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>777. Your 1044, November 27, 5 p.m.,<note n="25" xml:id="d728fn25">Not printed.</note> sections 2 and 3. Please comment on a
                                report which has been received by the Department that the French
                                Government has relinquished its rights in the Tangier zone and has
                                accepted Spanish control over that zone.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>